runava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Molyneux","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Irish (of Norman origin): occupational name from Old French <i>molineux</i> ‘miller’, a variant of <i>molineur</i>, <i>molinier</i>. See   Mulliner  .","English and Irish (of Norman origin): habitational name from an unidentified French placename.","Irish: adoption for   Mulligan  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Mullineaux","meanings":["Irish and English (Lancashire): variant of   Molyneux  ."]},{"name":"Mulliner","meanings":["English: occupational name for a miller, from Old French <i>molinier</i> ‘miller’. Compare   Molyneux  ."]},{"name":"Molineaux","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Staffordshire): variant of   Molyneux  ."]},{"name":"Molyneaux","meanings":["English and Irish (of Norman origin): variant of   Molyneux  . Compare   Mallonee  ."]}]},{"name":"Adam","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical.  See  <b>Adam</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":30,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":39,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Adam de Molyneux was born in 1185, in Sefton, Lancashire, England, his father, Richard de Molyneux, was 26 and his mother, Edith Pincerna Le Boteler, was 22. He married Letitia de Brinley in 1207, in Lancashire, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. In 1228, at the age of 43, his occupation is listed as commissioner of forests . He died in October 1246, in his hometown, at the age of 61."},"et":{"1185–October 1246":"1185–oktoober 1246","1183–Male":"1183–Surnud","1185–1246":"1185–1246","1187–Male":"1187–Surnud","1189–1220":"1189–1220","1210–1289":"1210–1289","1212–1287":"1212–1287","1159–1211":"1159–1211","1163–1187":"1163–1187","October 1246":"oktoober 1246","about 1181":"umbes 1181","1187":"1187","1220":"1220","1185":"1185","1163":"1163","1183":"1183","1228":"1228","1215":"1215","1159":"1159","1224":"1224","1246":"1246","1212":"1212","1289":"1289","1211":"1211","1189":"1189","1210":"1210","1287":"1287","about 1212":"umbes 1212","about 1220":"umbes 1220","1207":"1207","Sefton, West Derby, Lancashire, England":"Sefton, Lancashire, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England","Sefton, Lancashire, England":"Sefton, Lancashire, England","Little Crosby, Lancashire, England":"Little Crosby, Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"1185–October 1246":"1185–lokakuu 1246","1183–Male":"1183–Kuollut","1185–1246":"1185–1246","1187–Male":"1187–Kuollut","1189–1220":"1189–1220","1210–1289":"1210–1289","1212–1287":"1212–1287","1159–1211":"1159–1211","1163–1187":"1163–1187","October 1246":"lokakuu 1246","about 1181":"noin 1181","1187":"1187","1220":"1220","1185":"1185","1163":"1163","1183":"1183","1228":"1228","1215":"1215","1159":"1159","1224":"1224","1246":"1246","1212":"1212","1289":"1289","1211":"1211","1189":"1189","1210":"1210","1287":"1287","about 1212":"noin 1212","about 1220":"noin 1220","1207":"1207","Sefton, West Derby, Lancashire, England":"Sefton, Lancashire, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England","Sefton, Lancashire, England":"Sefton, Lancashire, England","Little Crosby, Lancashire, England":"Little Crosby, Lancashire, England"},"fr":{"1185–October 1246":"1185–octobre 1246","1183–Male":"1183–Décédé","1185–1246":"1185–1246","1187–Male":"1187–Décédé","1189–1220":"1189–1220","1210–1289":"1210–1289","1212–1287":"1212–1287","1159–1211":"1159–1211","1163–1187":"1163–1187","October 1246":"octobre 1246","about 1181":"environ 1181","1187":"1187","1220":"1220","1185":"1185","1163":"1163","1183":"1183","1228":"1228","1215":"1215","1159":"1159","1224":"1224","1246":"1246","1212":"1212","1289":"1289","1211":"1211","1189":"1189","1210":"1210","1287":"1287","about 1212":"environ 1212","about 1220":"environ 1220","1207":"1207","Sefton, West Derby, Lancashire, England":"Sefton, Lancashire, Angleterre","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, Angleterre","Sefton, Lancashire, England":"Sefton, Lancashire, Angleterre","Little Crosby, Lancashire, England":"Little Crosby, Lancashire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Adam de Molyneux est né en 1185, à Sefton, Lancashire, Angleterre, son père, Richard de Molyneux, avait 26 ans et sa mère, Edith Pincerna Le Boteler, avait 22 ans. Il a épousé Letitia de Brinley en 1207, à Lancashire, Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 2 fils. En 1228, à l’âge de 43 ans, sa profession de son indiquée est commissioner of forests . Il est décédé en octobre 1246, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 61 ans."},"de":{"1185–October 1246":"1185–Oktober 1246","1183–Male":"1183–Verstorben","1185–1246":"1185–1246","1187–Male":"1187–Verstorben","1189–1220":"1189–1220","1210–1289":"1210–1289","1212–1287":"1212–1287"